14/09/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police in the region are still looking for ten suspected members of a notorious Balkan criminal gang led by Darko Elez, Podgorica-based daily Dan reported on Sunday (September 13th), citing unnamed police sources.
The majority of the suspects are allegedly involved in drug trafficking.
Bosnian national Elez and more than 20 others were arrested on September 1st in a joint operation involving Serbian and Bosnian police.
They are suspected of murder, blackmail, robbery, drugs and weapons smuggling, and money laundering.
(B92, FoNet, RTRS, Srna, BHRT - 13/09/09)
